# Wiki Markup Parsing Patterns

## Infobox Parsing
The scraper recognizes these infobox types:
- `{{Technology infobox}}` - For technology items
- `{{Resource infobox}}` - For raw materials and resources
- `{{Product infobox}}` - For manufactured products
- `{{Item infobox}}` - For general items
- `{{Starship infobox}}` - For starships
- `{{Exocraft infobox}}` - For exocraft vehicles

Use regex pattern: `r'\{\{(Type) infobox\s*(.*?)\}\}'` with `re.DOTALL | re.IGNORECASE`

## Crafting Recipe Patterns
- `{{Craft|material1,amount1;material2,amount2}}` - Standard crafting
- `{{PoC-Repair|material1,amount1;material2,amount2}}` - Repair recipes
- `{{PoC-Dismantle|material1,amount1;material2,amount2}}` - Dismantle recipes
- `{{PoC-Refine|material,input;output;efficiency|description}}` - Refining recipes

## Description Extraction
Priority order for descriptions:
1. `==Game description==` section (preferred)
2. `==Summary==` section (fallback)

Clean markup by removing:
- Wiki links: `[[link|text]]` → `text`
- Bold markup: `'''text'''` → `text`
- Italic markup: `''text''` → `text`

## Category Extraction
Use pattern: `r'\[\[Category:([^\]]+)\]\]'` to extract all categories from page content.

## ID Generation
Generate consistent IDs using format: `{type}{TitleCamelCase}`
- Remove special characters from titles
- Convert to CamelCase
- Prefix with item type (e.g., "rawMaterials", "technology")